text: Robert Keith Wilson (22 November 1935 - 22 September 2020) was a top-ranking English tennis player. Wilson reached the quarterfinals of Wimbledon four times, Forest Hills twice, and Roland Garros once during the late 1950s and early 1960s. He was also a well known Great Britain Davis Cup team member. Wilson was born in Hendon, Middlesex. Wilson died on 22 September 2020 in Finchley, Middlesex at the age of 84.Former Great Britain Davis Cup player Bobby Wilson dies aged 84 ==References== Category:1935 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Male tennis players Category:Sportspeople from London
